## System Overview

The Blog and News microservice is a content management system that allows users to:
- Create, read, update travel blog posts
- Create, read, update news articles
- Upload multiple images per post
- Categorize blog posts with preset or custom categories
- Rate blog posts (0-5 stars with 0.5 precision)
- Track likes and comments (counts)
- Filter and sort posts by various criteria
- Share posts via social media

### Key Distinctions

**Blog Posts:**
- User-generated travel experiences
- Includes author information (name, avatar)
- Has rating, budget, category/tag, services
- Supports likes and comments
- Time displayed as relative (e.g., "2 hours ago", "yesterday")

**News Articles:**
- Official news/updates from sources
- Includes source organization name
- Has publication date (auto-generated on creation)
- No rating, budget, or services
- Time displayed as formatted date (e.g., "Oct 25, 2025")

---

## Entities and Data Models

### 1. Blog Entity

```typescript
interface Blog {
  id: string;                    // UUID or unique identifier
  author: string;                 // Author's full name
  avatar?: string;               // URL to author's avatar image
  title: string;                 // Blog post title (required)
  description: string;           // Full blog content/description (required)
  budget?: string;               // Optional budget (e.g., "$800")
  tag: string;                   // Category/tag (required)
  rating: number;                // Personal rating 0-5 (0.5 precision)
  images: string[];              // Array of image URLs
  services?: string[];          // Array of service names (max 6)
  likes?: number;                // Count of likes (default: 0)
  comments?: number;             // Count of comments (default: 0)
  createdAt: Date;               // Auto-generated creation timestamp
  updatedAt: Date;               // Auto-updated modification timestamp
  userId?: string;               // Reference to user who created (for authorization)
}
```

**Validation Rules:**
- `title`: Required, string, max 200 characters
- `description`: Required, string, max 5000 characters
- `budget`: Optional, string, max 50 characters
- `tag`: Required, string, max 100 characters
- `rating`: Required, number, 0-5, precision 0.5
- `images`: Array, max 10 images per post
- `services`: Array, max 6 services, each max 100 characters
- `author`: Required, string, max 100 characters
- `avatar`: Optional, valid image URL

**Preset Categories:**
- "Mountains & Hiking"
- "Beach & Coast"
- "Cultural Sites"
- "Food & Dining"
- "Adventure Sports"
- Custom categories are also allowed

---

### 2. News Entity

```typescript
interface News {
  id: string;                    // UUID or unique identifier
  source: string;                // News source organization (required)
  title: string;                 // News article title (required)
  summary: string;               // News summary/content (required)
  date: string;                  // Publication date (ISO 8601 format, auto-generated)
  images: string[];              // Array of image URLs
  url?: string;                  // Optional external URL
  createdAt: Date;              // Auto-generated creation timestamp
  updatedAt: Date;              // Auto-updated modification timestamp
  userId?: string;              // Reference to user who created (for authorization)
}
```

**Validation Rules:**
- `title`: Required, string, max 200 characters
- `summary`: Required, string, max 2000 characters
- `source`: Required, string, max 100 characters
- `date`: Auto-generated on creation (ISO 8601: "YYYY-MM-DDTHH:mm")
- `images`: Array, max 10 images per article
- `url`: Optional, valid URL format

**Important:** The `date` field is automatically set to the current timestamp when creating a news article. It should NOT be editable by users. When updating a news article, preserve the original `date` value.

---

### 3. Blog Image Entity (Optional - for better normalization)

```typescript
interface BlogImage {
  id: string;
  blogId: string;               // Foreign key to Blog
  imageUrl: string;             // URL to stored image
  order: number;                // Display order (0-based)
  createdAt: Date;
}
```

### 4. News Image Entity (Optional - for better normalization)

```typescript
interface NewsImage {
  id: string;
  newsId: string;               // Foreign key to News
  imageUrl: string;             // URL to stored image
  order: number;                // Display order (0-based)
  createdAt: Date;
}
```

### 5. Blog Service Entity (Optional - for better normalization)

```typescript
interface BlogService {
  id: string;
  blogId: string;               // Foreign key to Blog
  serviceName: string;          // Service name (e.g., "Tour Guide")
  order: number;                 // Display order
  createdAt: Date;
}
```

