## Database Schema (ER Diagram)

### Entity Relationship Diagram Description

```
┌─────────────┐
│    User     │ (if user management exists)
│─────────────│
│ id (PK)     │
│ ...         │
└──────┬──────┘
       │
       │ (1:N)
       │
┌──────▼──────┐         ┌──────────────┐
│    Blog     │         │  BlogImage   │
│─────────────│         │──────────────│
│ id (PK)     │◄────────│ id (PK)      │
│ userId (FK) │   1:N   │ blogId (FK)   │
│ author      │         │ imageUrl      │
│ avatar      │         │ order         │
│ title       │         └──────────────┘
│ description │
│ budget      │         ┌──────────────┐
│ tag         │         │ BlogService   │
│ rating      │         │──────────────│
│ likes       │         │ id (PK)      │
│ comments    │         │ blogId (FK)  │
│ createdAt   │◄────────│ serviceName  │
│ updatedAt   │   1:N   │ order        │
└─────────────┘         └──────────────┘

┌─────────────┐         ┌──────────────┐
│    News     │         │  NewsImage   │
│─────────────│         │──────────────│
│ id (PK)     │         │ id (PK)      │
│ userId (FK) │         │ newsId (FK)  │
│ source      │◄────────│ imageUrl     │
│ title       │   1:N   │ order        │
│ summary     │         └──────────────┘
│ date        │
│ url         │
│ createdAt   │
│ updatedAt   │
└─────────────┘
```

### Database Tables (SQL-like Schema)

#### Blogs Table
```sql
CREATE TABLE blogs (
    id VARCHAR(36) PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id VARCHAR(36),                    -- FK to users table (if exists)
    author VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
    avatar VARCHAR(500),                     -- URL to avatar image
    title VARCHAR(200) NOT NULL,
    description TEXT NOT NULL,               -- Up to 5000 chars
    budget VARCHAR(50),
    tag VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
    rating DECIMAL(2,1) NOT NULL DEFAULT 0, -- 0.0 to 5.0, precision 0.5
    likes INT DEFAULT 0,
    comments INT DEFAULT 0,
    created_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,
    updated_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP ON UPDATE CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,
    INDEX idx_user_id (user_id),
    INDEX idx_tag (tag),
    INDEX idx_rating (rating),
    INDEX idx_created_at (created_at)
);
```

#### News Table
```sql
CREATE TABLE news (
    id VARCHAR(36) PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id VARCHAR(36),                    -- FK to users table (if exists)
    source VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
    title VARCHAR(200) NOT NULL,
    summary TEXT NOT NULL,                   -- Up to 2000 chars
    date DATETIME NOT NULL,                 -- Auto-generated on creation
    url VARCHAR(500),
    created_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,
    updated_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP ON UPDATE CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,
    INDEX idx_user_id (user_id),
    INDEX idx_source (source),
    INDEX idx_date (date),
    INDEX idx_created_at (created_at)
);
```

#### Blog Images Table (Normalized Approach)
```sql
CREATE TABLE blog_images (
    id VARCHAR(36) PRIMARY KEY,
    blog_id VARCHAR(36) NOT NULL,
    image_url VARCHAR(500) NOT NULL,
    display_order INT NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,
    created_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,
    FOREIGN KEY (blog_id) REFERENCES blogs(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
    INDEX idx_blog_id (blog_id)
);
```

#### News Images Table (Normalized Approach)
```sql
CREATE TABLE news_images (
    id VARCHAR(36) PRIMARY KEY,
    news_id VARCHAR(36) NOT NULL,
    image_url VARCHAR(500) NOT NULL,
    display_order INT NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,
    created_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,
    FOREIGN KEY (news_id) REFERENCES news(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
    INDEX idx_news_id (news_id)
);
```

#### Blog Services Table (Normalized Approach)
```sql
CREATE TABLE blog_services (
    id VARCHAR(36) PRIMARY KEY,
    blog_id VARCHAR(36) NOT NULL,
    service_name VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
    display_order INT NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,
    created_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,
    FOREIGN KEY (blog_id) REFERENCES blogs(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
    INDEX idx_blog_id (blog_id)
);
```

**Alternative Approach (Denormalized):**
If you prefer simpler queries, you can store images and services as JSON arrays in the main tables:
- `blogs.images` as JSON array
- `blogs.services` as JSON array
- `news.images` as JSON array

---

## API Endpoints

### Base URL
```
/api/v1/blogs
```

### Blog Endpoints

#### 1. Get All Blogs
```
GET /api/v1/blogs
```

**Query Parameters:**
- `page` (optional): Page number for pagination (default: 1)
- `limit` (optional): Items per page (default: 20, max: 100)
- `tag` (optional): Filter by category/tag
- `sortBy` (optional): Sort order - "latest", "oldest", "rating-high", "rating-low" (default: "latest")
- `author` (optional): Filter by author name

**Response:**
```json
{
  "success": true,
  "data": [
    {
      "id": "uuid-here",
      "author": "Michael Chen",
      "avatar": "https://example.com/avatar.jpg",
      "title": "Mountain Hiking Adventure",
      "description": "An unforgettable hiking experience...",
      "budget": "$800",
      "tag": "Mountains & Hiking",
      "rating": 4.5,
      "images": ["url1", "url2"],
      "services": ["Tour Guide", "Camping Gear"],
      "likes": 189,
      "comments": 32,
      "createdAt": "2025-01-15T10:30:00Z",
      "updatedAt": "2025-01-15T10:30:00Z"
    }
  ],
  "pagination": {
    "page": 1,
    "limit": 20,
    "total": 100,
    "totalPages": 5
  }
}
```

#### 2. Get Blog by ID
```
GET /api/v1/blogs/:id
```

**Response:**
```json
{
  "success": true,
  "data": {
    "id": "uuid-here",
    "author": "Michael Chen",
    "avatar": "https://example.com/avatar.jpg",
    "title": "Mountain Hiking Adventure",
    "description": "Full description...",
    "budget": "$800",
    "tag": "Mountains & Hiking",
    "rating": 4.5,
    "images": ["url1", "url2"],
    "services": ["Tour Guide", "Camping Gear"],
    "likes": 189,
    "comments": 32,
    "createdAt": "2025-01-15T10:30:00Z",
    "updatedAt": "2025-01-15T10:30:00Z"
  }
}
```

#### 3. Create Blog
```
POST /api/v1/blogs
Content-Type: multipart/form-data
```

**Request Body (FormData):**
- `title` (string, required)
- `description` (string, required)
- `budget` (string, optional)
- `tag` (string, required)
- `author` (string, required)
- `avatar` (File or string URL, optional)
- `rating` (string number, required, 0-5)
- `services` (JSON string array, optional, max 6 items)
- `images` (File[], required, max 10 files)

**Response:**
```json
{
  "success": true,
  "data": {
    "id": "new-uuid",
    "author": "Michael Chen",
    "avatar": "https://example.com/avatar.jpg",
    "title": "Mountain Hiking Adventure",
    "description": "Full description...",
    "budget": "$800",
    "tag": "Mountains & Hiking",
    "rating": 4.5,
    "images": ["url1", "url2"],
    "services": ["Tour Guide", "Camping Gear"],
    "likes": 0,
    "comments": 0,
    "createdAt": "2025-01-15T10:30:00Z",
    "updatedAt": "2025-01-15T10:30:00Z"
  }
}
```

**Error Response:**
```json
{
  "success": false,
  "message": "Validation error",
  "errors": {
    "title": "Title is required",
    "rating": "Rating must be between 0 and 5"
  }
}
```

#### 4. Update Blog
```
PATCH /api/v1/blogs/:id
Content-Type: multipart/form-data
```

**Request Body:** Same as Create Blog (all fields optional except validation)

**Response:** Same as Create Blog

#### 5. Delete Blog (Optional - not in frontend but recommended)
```
DELETE /api/v1/blogs/:id
```

